1
00:00:00,689 --> 00:00:03,551
[♪♪♪]

2
00:00:36,965 --> 00:00:39,068
[GASPS]
[DOG BARKING]

3
00:00:48,586 --> 00:00:49,724
[GASPS]

4
00:00:49,862 --> 00:00:51,827
[DOG BARKING, GROWLING]

5
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,275
Come on.

6
00:00:55,413 --> 00:00:58,206
I think I've had enough
of this city for one day.

7
00:01:36,379 --> 00:01:39,517
I'll ask you again,
Mr. Capello...

8
00:01:39,655 --> 00:01:42,862
or do you prefer DeAndria,
or Nicky the Knife?

9
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:44,586
I lose track
with all your aliases.

10
00:01:44,724 --> 00:01:46,000
I object, Your Honor.

11
00:01:46,137 --> 00:01:48,344
I think by now
defense counsel is familiar

12
00:01:48,482 --> 00:01:50,344
with the witness' name.

13
00:01:50,482 --> 00:01:52,965
I expect closing arguments
today, Mr. Stein,

14
00:01:53,103 --> 00:01:54,827
so please skip the theatrics

15
00:01:54,965 --> 00:01:58,172
you've so adroitly managed to
slip in during this entire trial

16
00:01:58,310 --> 00:02:00,344
and ask your question.

17
00:02:00,482 --> 00:02:03,620
Mr. Capello, you have admitted

18
00:02:03,758 --> 00:02:05,758
that you have killed
on occasion.

19
00:02:05,896 --> 00:02:07,724
On Ringerman's orders.

20
00:02:07,862 --> 00:02:09,344
[GALLERY MURMURING]

21
00:02:09,482 --> 00:02:12,517
You've also told us you've lied
for Mr. Ringerman in the past.

22
00:02:12,655 --> 00:02:13,862
Hey, I'm a stand-up guy.

23
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,620
I work for somebody,
I work for 'em,

24
00:02:15,758 --> 00:02:18,206
no matter what it takes.
Yet you're here today

25
00:02:18,344 --> 00:02:20,000
trying to put Mr. Ringerman
in jail

26
00:02:20,137 --> 00:02:21,793
for a crime he did not commit.

27
00:02:21,931 --> 00:02:24,448
He committed it. I saw it.
I was there.

28
00:02:24,586 --> 00:02:25,965
You admit you lie?

29
00:02:26,103 --> 00:02:29,103
Why should the jury assume
that you're not lying to them?

30
00:02:29,241 --> 00:02:31,000
Because I ain't.

31
00:02:32,482 --> 00:02:34,241
Don't insult the court,
Mr. Capello.

32
00:02:34,379 --> 00:02:36,689
Did you or did you not
make a deal with the DA's office

33
00:02:36,827 --> 00:02:38,206
in return for your testimony?

34
00:02:38,344 --> 00:02:39,896
UNDERWOOD:
Objection.
That has no bearing.

35
00:02:40,034 --> 00:02:41,448
If you're working
for the DA now

36
00:02:41,586 --> 00:02:43,896
like you did for Mr. Ringerman,
would you lie for the DA?

37
00:02:44,034 --> 00:02:45,310
Objection!
Would you lie

38
00:02:45,448 --> 00:02:47,241
to stay out of jail
like in the past?

39
00:02:47,379 --> 00:02:49,034
I object!

40
00:02:49,172 --> 00:02:50,482
Sustained.

41
00:02:50,620 --> 00:02:52,206
Counsels, approach the bench.

42
00:02:52,344 --> 00:02:53,724
[GALLERY MURMURING]

43
00:02:53,862 --> 00:02:55,344
He got us good.

44
00:02:56,586 --> 00:02:58,379
We still have our last witness.

45
00:03:00,068 --> 00:03:04,344
[♪♪♪]

46
00:03:04,482 --> 00:03:06,896
Closing arguments
immediately after recess.

47
00:03:07,034 --> 00:03:09,068
UNDERWOOD:
I have one more
rebuttal witness.

48
00:03:09,206 --> 00:03:11,758
STEIN:
I know nothing
of any other witness. I object.

49
00:03:11,896 --> 00:03:14,862
UNDERWOOD: 
This witness was afraid. 
She feared for her life

50
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,827
and would not come forward 
until today.

51
00:03:16,965 --> 00:03:19,068
Mr. Stein knows 
who this witness is by name,

52
00:03:19,206 --> 00:03:21,068
and he knows 
what she will do to his case

53
00:03:21,206 --> 00:03:22,758
if he keeps 
her from testifying.

54
00:03:22,896 --> 00:03:24,827
JUDGE: 
If you feel 
this witness's testimony

55
00:03:24,965 --> 00:03:27,965
will have that much effect 
on the case, bring her forth.

56
00:03:37,344 --> 00:03:40,206
The court calls
Madilyn Dougherty to the stand.

57
00:03:40,344 --> 00:03:43,724
[REPORTERS CLAMORING]
[CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING]

58
00:03:45,241 --> 00:03:47,620
I don't know, Dan.
Something's wrong with her.

59
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:07,655
BAILIFF: 
Do you solemnly affirm to tell 
the truth, the whole truth

60
00:04:07,793 --> 00:04:09,275
and nothing but the truth?
MADILYN: I do.

61
00:04:09,413 --> 00:04:10,689
UNDERWOOD: 
Miss Dougherty...

62
00:04:10,827 --> 00:04:12,310
will you please
tell the court

63
00:04:12,448 --> 00:04:15,068
exactly what you told
my assistant early this morning?

64
00:04:24,137 --> 00:04:25,448
I...

65
00:04:27,034 --> 00:04:29,068
I...
Take your time, Miss Dougherty.

66
00:04:30,896 --> 00:04:33,517
No one is going to hurt you.

67
00:04:33,655 --> 00:04:35,103
Just speak the truth.

68
00:04:36,586 --> 00:04:39,275
Please tell the court your
connection to Mr. Ringerman.

69
00:04:39,413 --> 00:04:40,896
I...

70
00:04:42,103 --> 00:04:43,103
don't have one.

71
00:04:44,758 --> 00:04:47,586
You don't have-- Miss Dougherty,

72
00:04:47,724 --> 00:04:50,931
don't you work for the Argent
Corporation as a bookkeeper?

73
00:04:51,068 --> 00:04:53,689
And didn't you, while working
with the company ledgers,

74
00:04:53,827 --> 00:04:56,000
come across evidence that proves

75
00:04:56,137 --> 00:04:59,310
that Mr. Ringerman not only is
a secret owner of the company

76
00:04:59,448 --> 00:05:01,482
but that the company itself
is nothing more

77
00:05:01,620 --> 00:05:03,931
than a money laundering front
for Mr. Ringerman?

78
00:05:04,068 --> 00:05:06,413
I know nothing
about any of that,

79
00:05:06,551 --> 00:05:07,689
and I have no proof.

80
00:05:09,551 --> 00:05:12,758
[GALLERY MURMURING]
Miss Dougherty,

81
00:05:12,896 --> 00:05:16,172
you told my assistant something
very different this morning.

82
00:05:16,310 --> 00:05:18,206
I was mistaken.

83
00:05:18,344 --> 00:05:19,655
How could you be mistaken?

84
00:05:19,793 --> 00:05:21,931
You came forward voluntarily.

85
00:05:22,068 --> 00:05:26,103
I was confused. I was mistaken.

86
00:05:26,241 --> 00:05:29,034
I don't know anything
about Mr. Ringerman.

87
00:05:29,172 --> 00:05:31,586
Your Honor, this witness is
obviously terrified.

88
00:05:31,724 --> 00:05:33,137
I object.

89
00:05:33,275 --> 00:05:35,689
There is no evidence to
support counsel's statement.

90
00:05:35,827 --> 00:05:38,275
I have to agree with Mr. Stein.

91
00:05:38,413 --> 00:05:40,275
Does the witness realize
the seriousness

92
00:05:40,413 --> 00:05:44,034
of perjuring her admission
to the DA's office this morning?

93
00:05:44,172 --> 00:05:47,206
[♪♪♪]

94
00:05:48,724 --> 00:05:51,689
I don't know anything...

95
00:05:51,827 --> 00:05:54,827
Anything about
Mr. Ringerman's business.

96
00:05:54,965 --> 00:05:56,310
REPORTER:
Here they come.

97
00:05:56,448 --> 00:05:58,310
Mr. Ringerman, can you give me
anything for the evening news?

98
00:05:58,448 --> 00:06:00,655
We were confident
in the legal system all along

99
00:06:00,793 --> 00:06:02,724
and in the jury.
Can I have a comment?

100
00:06:02,862 --> 00:06:04,965
Mr. Ringerman has no comment
to make at this time.

101
00:06:05,103 --> 00:06:08,448
Thank you very much.
No further comment, thank you.

102
00:06:08,586 --> 00:06:11,000
Thank you very much.
[REPORTERS CLAMORING]

103
00:06:17,551 --> 00:06:19,586
I don't know what to say.

104
00:06:19,724 --> 00:06:21,931
Whatever there was to say,
it should've been said in here.

105
00:06:22,068 --> 00:06:24,758
I understand if you press
charges against me.

106
00:06:24,896 --> 00:06:26,620
I think we're done
pressing charges

107
00:06:26,758 --> 00:06:29,827
in any matters
regarding Thomas Ringerman.

108
00:06:29,965 --> 00:06:31,758
We had our shot.

109
00:06:31,896 --> 00:06:34,137
Justice wasn't on our side.

110
00:06:35,862 --> 00:06:38,793
[♪♪♪]

111
00:07:36,931 --> 00:07:39,862
[♪♪♪]

112
00:07:56,068 --> 00:07:58,172
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

113
00:08:04,517 --> 00:08:05,551
Hello?

114
00:08:05,689 --> 00:08:07,172
MAN: 
You follow directions well.

115
00:08:07,310 --> 00:08:08,655
Very well.

116
00:08:08,793 --> 00:08:10,620
All right, now let him go.

117
00:08:10,758 --> 00:08:12,689
I did exactly what you wanted.

118
00:08:12,827 --> 00:08:14,379
Now let my brother go.

119
00:08:14,517 --> 00:08:16,068
Just continue 
to do as you're told,

120
00:08:16,206 --> 00:08:17,689
and you'll get 
what you want.

121
00:08:17,827 --> 00:08:18,965
That's the way it works.

122
00:08:19,103 --> 00:08:20,586
I did what you wanted.
You said--

123
00:08:20,724 --> 00:08:25,586
I said do as you're told! 
You're not done doing that.

124
00:08:25,724 --> 00:08:27,103
Get a pen and piece of paper.

125
00:08:27,241 --> 00:08:30,137
Write this down, 
because if you forget,

126
00:08:30,275 --> 00:08:33,896
you'll have no way of reaching 
your brother ever again.

127
00:08:34,034 --> 00:08:36,068
Along the pier 
near 10th Street,

128
00:08:36,206 --> 00:08:37,965
walk past the warehouse

129
00:08:38,103 --> 00:08:40,931
with the old Cavanaugh 
Maritime and Salvage sign.

130
00:08:41,068 --> 00:08:42,896
Hope to see you there,

131
00:08:43,034 --> 00:08:46,620
but probably not as much 
as your brother does.

132
00:08:46,758 --> 00:08:48,379
And be careful.

133
00:08:48,517 --> 00:08:50,379
It's not a neighborhood 
for a pretty lady

134
00:08:50,517 --> 00:08:52,724
to be wandering around in 
at night.

135
00:08:52,862 --> 00:08:54,965
[LINE CLICKS, THEN DIAL TONE]

136
00:08:56,172 --> 00:08:59,068
[♪♪♪]

137
00:09:05,448 --> 00:09:08,034
Remember telling ghost stories
as a kid?

138
00:09:09,620 --> 00:09:11,310
Remember turning
all the lights off

139
00:09:11,448 --> 00:09:14,344
and huddling together
with a flashlight

140
00:09:14,482 --> 00:09:19,517
and trying to dream up
the worst nightmares possible?

141
00:09:19,655 --> 00:09:23,586
Well, I bet you've never
dreamt up anything like me.

142
00:09:23,724 --> 00:09:25,896
We're gonna have a scary time.

143
00:09:26,034 --> 00:09:28,137
Me, you...

144
00:09:28,275 --> 00:09:30,482
and your sister.

145
00:09:30,620 --> 00:09:32,482
[WHISTLES]

146
00:09:32,620 --> 00:09:35,137
[LAUGHING]

147
00:09:35,275 --> 00:09:36,655
I love this crap.

148
00:09:36,793 --> 00:09:38,827
SONNY:
Good to see you laughin'
again, Tommy.

149
00:09:38,965 --> 00:09:41,689
It's been a while.
That judge took care of you.

150
00:09:41,827 --> 00:09:43,793
He didn't give that DA an inch.

151
00:09:43,931 --> 00:09:45,758
It wouldn't have been
the same last year

152
00:09:45,896 --> 00:09:47,724
if Cain had been on the bench.

153
00:09:47,862 --> 00:09:50,965
I don't get nervous about
little girls with big mouths.

154
00:09:51,103 --> 00:09:53,379
I don't get nervous
about dead men.

155
00:09:53,517 --> 00:09:55,344
If I had to worry
about dead men,

156
00:09:55,482 --> 00:09:58,620
I'd have 10 times
as many worries as I have now.

157
00:09:58,758 --> 00:10:01,137
Some guys think, you know,
he's still around.

158
00:10:01,275 --> 00:10:02,655
I mean, you must've heard.

159
00:10:02,793 --> 00:10:04,137
Toomey says it was Judge Cain

160
00:10:04,275 --> 00:10:06,310
who nailed him and
Patty Boxcars last month.

161
00:10:06,448 --> 00:10:07,758
[CHUCKLES]

162
00:10:07,896 --> 00:10:10,413
Toomey's doing his time
at the state laughing academy.

163
00:10:10,551 --> 00:10:12,758
You don't think
he was serious, do you?

164
00:10:12,896 --> 00:10:14,310
He didn't wanna do hard time,

165
00:10:14,448 --> 00:10:17,620
so he came up with that
"Cain still being alive" garbage

166
00:10:17,758 --> 00:10:20,310
to help him
cop a plea for soft walls.

167
00:10:20,448 --> 00:10:23,586
He'll be out in a few years
with pottery he made for us all.

168
00:10:23,724 --> 00:10:25,448
He never said Cain
was still alive.

169
00:10:25,586 --> 00:10:26,689
Enough!

170
00:10:29,068 --> 00:10:30,896
She's here.

171
00:10:31,034 --> 00:10:32,482
[CHUCKLING]

172
00:10:42,206 --> 00:10:45,103
[♪♪♪]

173
00:10:51,965 --> 00:10:54,068
[THUNDER CRASHES]

174
00:10:55,379 --> 00:10:57,655
[RINGERMAN LAUGHING]

175
00:10:59,482 --> 00:11:03,827
Madilyn, we were just talking
about coming back from the dead,

176
00:11:03,965 --> 00:11:06,517
and you and your brother
can give us a firsthand report

177
00:11:06,655 --> 00:11:08,586
whether or not that's possible.

178
00:11:10,034 --> 00:11:12,517
Just let Patrick go.

179
00:11:12,655 --> 00:11:16,896
Please.
Please just let him go.

180
00:11:17,034 --> 00:11:20,034
He won't--
He can't do anything to you.

181
00:11:20,172 --> 00:11:22,310
You're so right.

182
00:11:22,448 --> 00:11:25,103
No one can do anything to me.

183
00:11:25,241 --> 00:11:29,379
Not your brother, not you,
not the police...

184
00:11:29,517 --> 00:11:31,206
not even ghosts.

185
00:11:31,344 --> 00:11:33,551
[LAUGHING]

186
00:11:33,689 --> 00:11:35,758
[THUNDER CRASHES]

187
00:11:35,896 --> 00:11:37,862
What the hell?!

188
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,206
Boo!

189
00:11:42,793 --> 00:11:44,758
See a ghost?
No, I-- Heh-heh.

190
00:11:44,896 --> 00:11:49,310
Hey, I just, uh-- Makin' sure
she didn't bring anybody.

191
00:11:49,448 --> 00:11:51,103
She didn't bring anybody.

192
00:11:53,172 --> 00:11:54,413
Did you, Madilyn?

193
00:11:55,896 --> 00:11:59,068
No.
[THUNDER CRASHING]

194
00:11:59,206 --> 00:12:01,000
She knows better than that.

195
00:12:03,931 --> 00:12:06,068
What about m-my brother?

196
00:12:07,413 --> 00:12:09,137
Go kill him.

197
00:12:10,827 --> 00:12:12,827
Make him scream loud enough
for her to hear.

198
00:12:12,965 --> 00:12:14,448
No! No, no!

199
00:12:14,586 --> 00:12:17,103
[MADILYN SCREAMING]

200
00:12:19,413 --> 00:12:21,068
[RINGERMAN LAUGHING]

201
00:12:23,034 --> 00:12:26,931
Hey, did you guys give him
a new wardrobe to be buried in?

202
00:12:33,827 --> 00:12:37,241
[♪♪♪]

203
00:12:37,379 --> 00:12:38,620
What the hell is this?.

204
00:12:38,758 --> 00:12:40,827
[GROANING]

205
00:13:03,620 --> 00:13:04,793
Jilly?

206
00:13:18,137 --> 00:13:19,551
[BEEPING]

207
00:13:24,034 --> 00:13:26,137
Tommy? Tommy, you there?

208
00:13:26,275 --> 00:13:27,379
Shut up! Keep quiet.

209
00:13:34,862 --> 00:13:36,241
[MUFFLED GASPING]

210
00:13:40,482 --> 00:13:42,310
Your brother is safe.

211
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:50,965
Whoever the hell you are,

212
00:13:51,103 --> 00:13:53,275
there better be
more than one of you!

213
00:14:02,724 --> 00:14:04,551
What the hell
do you think you're doing?

214
00:14:04,689 --> 00:14:06,448
MAN:
I accuse Thomas Ringerman,

215
00:14:06,586 --> 00:14:09,586
head of the largest drug-
smuggling racket in the city,

216
00:14:09,724 --> 00:14:11,103
personally responsible

217
00:14:11,241 --> 00:14:14,482
for hundreds of thousands of
ruined lives, children's deaths,

218
00:14:14,620 --> 00:14:17,379
all caused by the poison
you import and sell.

219
00:14:17,517 --> 00:14:20,275
You, Thomas Ringerman,
I find guilty!

220
00:14:20,413 --> 00:14:22,000
And I find you dead!

221
00:14:34,793 --> 00:14:37,482
MAN:
I accuse Ramon "Sonny" Santiago.

222
00:14:37,620 --> 00:14:41,172
I charge you with extortion,
drug smuggling, kidnapping,

223
00:14:41,310 --> 00:14:45,620
attempted murder and murder.
And you, too, I find guilty.

224
00:14:45,758 --> 00:14:47,034
What the--?

225
00:14:53,620 --> 00:14:55,379
[THUNDER CRASHES]

226
00:15:03,655 --> 00:15:05,068
[GRUNTS]

227
00:15:05,206 --> 00:15:07,655
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

228
00:15:23,034 --> 00:15:25,206
What did you do to him?

229
00:15:27,931 --> 00:15:32,310
Okay, man. Okay, what is this?
What are you doing?

230
00:15:32,448 --> 00:15:34,172
Who are you?

231
00:15:34,310 --> 00:15:36,965
MAN:
I'm your judge and jury.

232
00:15:37,103 --> 00:15:40,068
And if necessary,
I'm your executioner.

233
00:15:40,206 --> 00:15:42,586
You're crazy!

234
00:15:42,724 --> 00:15:45,275
[MAN LAUGHING]
[TRIGGER CLICKING]

235
00:15:50,689 --> 00:15:51,620
[YELPS]

236
00:15:53,448 --> 00:15:54,793
[WHIRRING]

237
00:15:54,931 --> 00:15:57,655
What the hell are you?
You're a robot.

238
00:15:57,793 --> 00:15:59,448
You're a damned robot!

239
00:15:59,586 --> 00:16:01,206
No, Ringerman.

240
00:16:01,344 --> 00:16:03,655
I'm a ghost story.

241
00:16:05,724 --> 00:16:07,689
[SCREAMING]

242
00:16:12,931 --> 00:16:17,103
I confess to the charges of 
kidnapping Patrick Dougherty.

243
00:16:18,862 --> 00:16:20,448
Kidnapping him 
with the intent

244
00:16:20,586 --> 00:16:25,068
of forcing Madilyn Dougherty 
to change her testimony.

245
00:16:25,206 --> 00:16:28,241
Her testimony 
would've sunk me.

246
00:16:28,379 --> 00:16:30,172
And I knew, 
to save her brother's life,

247
00:16:30,310 --> 00:16:32,068
she would do anything...

248
00:16:33,655 --> 00:16:37,931
even lie in open court.

249
00:16:38,068 --> 00:16:40,482
Right there, "to save his life."
That's it.

250
00:16:40,620 --> 00:16:43,517
He admits he was planning
to kill him.

251
00:16:43,655 --> 00:16:47,482
You're going to have to go over
this again and again and again,

252
00:16:47,620 --> 00:16:49,379
here and in court.

253
00:16:49,517 --> 00:16:53,275
You have no idea who it was
who gave you this videotape,

254
00:16:53,413 --> 00:16:54,758
who it was that saved you?

255
00:16:54,896 --> 00:16:58,103
I mean, mystery men who
materialize from the night sky

256
00:16:58,241 --> 00:16:59,620
don't cut it for a jury,

257
00:16:59,758 --> 00:17:03,413
and this testimony could
get thrown out, except...

258
00:17:03,551 --> 00:17:06,310
Except what?
Except when I contacted Stein,

259
00:17:06,448 --> 00:17:08,068
Ringerman's attorney,
this morning,

260
00:17:08,206 --> 00:17:10,931
he'd already spoken
with his client.

261
00:17:11,068 --> 00:17:13,379
Ringerman wants to try
to make a deal.

262
00:17:13,517 --> 00:17:16,482
He's not even trying to say he
was coerced into a confession?

263
00:17:16,620 --> 00:17:18,689
No, he's not.

264
00:17:18,827 --> 00:17:22,034
Which makes no sense.
It makes no damn sense at all.

265
00:17:22,172 --> 00:17:24,172
Unless he's afraid.

266
00:17:24,310 --> 00:17:25,931
More afraid than going to jail.

267
00:17:26,068 --> 00:17:27,862
Afraid of what, though?
Of who?

268
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,724
Of ghosts.

269
00:17:31,310 --> 00:17:32,862
Ghosts?

270
00:17:34,517 --> 00:17:37,413
[♪♪♪]

271
00:18:11,310 --> 00:18:13,551
[CHIMING SOFTLY]

272
00:18:15,517 --> 00:18:16,724
[BEEPING]

273
00:18:20,689 --> 00:18:23,068
[TV BROADCASTS OVERLAPPING]

274
00:19:08,793 --> 00:19:10,655
RAE:
From what I hear
of Tommy Ringerman,

275
00:19:10,793 --> 00:19:13,103
he won't give up
till he sees you dead.

276
00:19:13,241 --> 00:19:14,896
He already has.

277
00:19:17,931 --> 00:19:20,172
You spook me too
when you get this way, judge.

278
00:19:20,310 --> 00:19:22,172
A word of friendly advice.

279
00:19:22,310 --> 00:19:25,931
You're gettin' off on this
Dark Avenger gig way too much.

280
00:19:26,068 --> 00:19:29,551
Computers, electronics,
even some makeup.

281
00:19:29,689 --> 00:19:31,103
I didn't know your expertise

282
00:19:31,241 --> 00:19:33,896
spilled over
into psychoanalysis.

283
00:19:34,034 --> 00:19:36,655
Just, uh, stuff I pick up
from the prison shrink

284
00:19:36,793 --> 00:19:39,000
and the freako movies
I used to see as a kid.

285
00:19:39,137 --> 00:19:41,965
All them deformed guys start
to go bonkers after a while.

286
00:19:42,103 --> 00:19:44,517
It's strain from having
to hide in the dark so long.

287
00:19:44,655 --> 00:19:46,172
The only strain I might feel

288
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:48,931
is having to put up
with this thrift-shop equipment

289
00:19:49,068 --> 00:19:50,724
you send me out there with.

290
00:19:50,862 --> 00:19:54,689
Hey, hey, hey,
thrift shop, my tuchus.

291
00:19:54,827 --> 00:19:59,206
I use the same components you
find in anything made by Sony.

292
00:19:59,344 --> 00:20:02,551
Well, when I want to take on
the criminal element with a VCR,

293
00:20:02,689 --> 00:20:04,275
I'll call.

294
00:20:08,241 --> 00:20:09,517
Oh, wait, what'd you do,

295
00:20:09,655 --> 00:20:11,586
downfield block
an express train?

296
00:20:11,724 --> 00:20:13,275
Hey, one of Ringerman's
associates

297
00:20:13,413 --> 00:20:17,310
tried to take off my arm
with a pipe.

298
00:20:17,448 --> 00:20:20,241
How much longer you think you
can get away with this, judge?

299
00:20:20,379 --> 00:20:23,655
I mean, sooner or later,
someone's gonna figure you out.

300
00:20:23,793 --> 00:20:25,896
No one will figure me out.

301
00:20:26,034 --> 00:20:28,448
Not unless somebody tells 'em.

302
00:20:28,586 --> 00:20:30,827
Don't run that rap on me.
I'd be doin' hard time

303
00:20:30,965 --> 00:20:34,034
on the dark side of Pluto
if not for you. I just...

304
00:20:34,172 --> 00:20:35,758
Speakin' of which,
I gotta get back

305
00:20:35,896 --> 00:20:38,724
to my nice, safe cell tonight
or I'm gonna get in deep guano

306
00:20:38,862 --> 00:20:40,655
and blow the work furlough
you got me.

307
00:20:40,793 --> 00:20:42,206
You should've left.

308
00:20:42,344 --> 00:20:44,137
Nah, I just wanted
to finish up some work

309
00:20:44,275 --> 00:20:46,034
on this new tear-gas pellet.

310
00:20:46,172 --> 00:20:48,896
I think I found a way we can
load it under the laser.

311
00:20:55,517 --> 00:20:57,310
What would you say
if I could put you

312
00:20:57,448 --> 00:21:00,068
into all the police
interrogation rooms at Central?

313
00:21:04,068 --> 00:21:05,482
They cabled up the building

314
00:21:05,620 --> 00:21:07,000
and all the cameras
are centrally linked.

315
00:21:07,137 --> 00:21:09,068
And you say
you're not into all this?

316
00:21:09,206 --> 00:21:10,724
Oh, don't get me wrong,
you know.

317
00:21:10,862 --> 00:21:12,689
I'm not into throwin' on
strange get-ups

318
00:21:12,827 --> 00:21:15,413
and scarin' the crap
out of bad guys with a whisper,

319
00:21:15,551 --> 00:21:17,172
but you and me, we're like...

320
00:21:17,310 --> 00:21:19,482
Courageous Cat
and Minute Mouse.

321
00:21:19,620 --> 00:21:23,448
Why, Rae, be careful.
Your emotions are showing.

322
00:21:23,586 --> 00:21:25,655
I don't care any farther
than being concerned

323
00:21:25,793 --> 00:21:28,379
with who gets all this
if you don't come back one day.

324
00:21:28,517 --> 00:21:30,137
I mean, I built all this stuff.

325
00:21:30,275 --> 00:21:33,344
I feel, you know, owner-like.

326
00:21:33,482 --> 00:21:35,862
Except for however many of those
hats you got layin' around,

327
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:38,379
which I would not be
caught dead in.

328
00:21:39,448 --> 00:21:40,965
Scratch that.

329
00:21:41,103 --> 00:21:42,448
But I don't know what happens

330
00:21:42,586 --> 00:21:44,586
once you walk out
your secret panel there.

331
00:21:44,724 --> 00:21:48,275
Now, like this Ringerman.
He can be a real bad dude.

332
00:21:50,034 --> 00:21:51,620
So can I.

333
00:21:51,758 --> 00:21:53,689
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

334
00:22:22,103 --> 00:22:25,034
[SCREAMING]

335
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:39,310
REPORTER [ON TV]: 
The Grim Reaper 
has struck again.

336
00:22:39,448 --> 00:22:41,793
Police say the Reaper 
claimed his fourth victim

337
00:22:41,931 --> 00:22:44,586
earlier this evening in 
the exclusive Oakhurst District

338
00:22:44,724 --> 00:22:45,862
of the city.

339
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:47,586
Like the other Reaper victims,

340
00:22:47,724 --> 00:22:52,586
Janis Elwick was in her early 
20s, attractive and alone.

341
00:22:52,724 --> 00:22:55,344
[BROADCAST CONTINUES
INDISTINCTLY]

342
00:23:01,827 --> 00:23:04,206
Is that like
a King Kong laser or what?

343
00:23:04,344 --> 00:23:07,724
Anyway, here are the blueprints
to Central Division downtown.

344
00:23:12,620 --> 00:23:14,241
I think if we mount
a microwave dish

345
00:23:14,379 --> 00:23:16,137
on a building
above the west side,

346
00:23:16,275 --> 00:23:19,310
we can pull in
from the main terminal.

347
00:23:19,448 --> 00:23:21,034
Yes, no, maybe? 
Until now,

348
00:23:21,172 --> 00:23:23,103
there has been no indication 
by the police

349
00:23:23,241 --> 00:23:25,310
that there have been 
any suspects in the case.

350
00:23:25,448 --> 00:23:27,655
Indeed, that there 
have been any leads at all.

351
00:23:27,793 --> 00:23:30,655
But tonight Captain Strauss 
has implied otherwise.

352
00:23:30,793 --> 00:23:32,310
Oy vey.Heh.

353
00:23:32,448 --> 00:23:34,931
You can't wait for that one
to be on trial, can you?

354
00:23:35,068 --> 00:23:37,379
On the warpath again.
We put one to bed,

355
00:23:37,517 --> 00:23:40,310
and already you're lookin'
to be back on the case.

356
00:23:40,448 --> 00:23:42,758
I might be back on the case.

357
00:23:42,896 --> 00:23:44,931
You're gonna be back in jail.

358
00:23:49,068 --> 00:23:50,413
[ENGINE POWERING UP]

359
00:23:50,551 --> 00:23:52,862
Turbines to speed,
batteries to power,

360
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:54,275
bat thrusters ready.

361
00:23:54,413 --> 00:23:55,551
[CHUCKLES]

362
00:23:57,517 --> 00:24:00,379
When we do this,
I can't resist, heh.

363
00:24:00,517 --> 00:24:02,620
See, Rae, talk to your shrink.

364
00:24:02,758 --> 00:24:05,448
There's a little Lone Ranger
in all of us.

365
00:24:07,379 --> 00:24:10,275
[♪♪♪]

366
00:24:28,172 --> 00:24:30,586
[♪♪♪]

367
00:24:33,379 --> 00:24:35,655
We spoke earlier today 
with Captain David Strauss

368
00:24:35,793 --> 00:24:37,620
and Commissioner 
Peter Kinghorn.

369
00:24:37,758 --> 00:24:40,517
KINGHORN: 
The entire police department 
was caught off guard

370
00:24:40,655 --> 00:24:42,931
by this turnaround 
in the Thomas Ringerman case,

371
00:24:43,068 --> 00:24:44,413
but as long as truth prevails

372
00:24:44,551 --> 00:24:45,965
and matters reach 
their proper end,

373
00:24:46,103 --> 00:24:47,448
then justice has been served.

374
00:24:47,586 --> 00:24:49,379
The department is here 
to see that happens.

375
00:24:49,517 --> 00:24:51,931
REPORTER: 
What about the Grim Reaper? 
Is it true you have a suspect?

376
00:24:52,068 --> 00:24:54,379
I'll address that 
later today, all right?

377
00:24:54,517 --> 00:24:56,758
REPORTER: 
There's a rumor 
that you have a confession.

378
00:24:56,896 --> 00:24:58,965
Like I said, there'll be 
a formal explanation

379
00:24:59,103 --> 00:25:00,379
from Captain Strauss 
later today.

380
00:25:00,517 --> 00:25:02,620
Now, thank you very much. 
No more questions.

381
00:25:02,758 --> 00:25:05,206
REPORTER: But, commissioner--
Just once I'm dyin' to see you

382
00:25:05,344 --> 00:25:07,448
catch a couple of minutes
of Wheel of Fortune

383
00:25:07,586 --> 00:25:09,689
or Pink Panther
or something truly frivolous,

384
00:25:09,827 --> 00:25:11,793
like a guy in a black hat
would watch.

385
00:25:11,931 --> 00:25:14,241
I mean, you have seen 
Casablanca,haven't you?

386
00:25:15,586 --> 00:25:17,275
Everyone's seen 
Casablanca,right?

387
00:25:20,206 --> 00:25:23,103
[♪♪♪]

388
00:25:34,517 --> 00:25:36,965
You know, not that
I'm crazy about this gig,

389
00:25:37,103 --> 00:25:39,586
but, uh, we never
have any company picnics,

390
00:25:39,724 --> 00:25:43,275
office Christmas parties,
no softball league.

391
00:25:43,413 --> 00:25:45,310
You think we take our jobs
too seriously?

392
00:25:45,448 --> 00:25:47,172
I never get
an end-of-the-year bonus.

393
00:25:47,310 --> 00:25:49,448
Well, we haven't been together
for a year yet.

394
00:25:49,586 --> 00:25:52,620
Oh, well, let's chalk that up
to a subtle reminder, then.

395
00:25:56,344 --> 00:25:58,793
You wanna come in?
Meet the gang?

396
00:25:58,931 --> 00:26:00,862
As a matter of fact,
you know some of 'em.

397
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:03,379
You put 'em here. Bunch of 'em
would probably love

398
00:26:03,517 --> 00:26:06,206
to make you
a personalized license plate.

399
00:26:06,344 --> 00:26:07,724
Send my regards for me.

400
00:26:09,517 --> 00:26:12,137
Mention how close we are,
you and I.

401
00:26:14,827 --> 00:26:17,103
You're gonna check up
on this Grim Reaper?

402
00:26:17,241 --> 00:26:21,448
That means goin' to Kinghorn's.
Why don't you let me do that?

403
00:26:21,586 --> 00:26:24,413
If Kinghorn finds out you're not
at the bottom of the river,

404
00:26:24,551 --> 00:26:27,413
he'll be more dangerous for you
than any 10 gals in here...

405
00:26:28,896 --> 00:26:30,620
not to mention your daughter.

406
00:26:32,482 --> 00:26:35,000
[♪♪♪]

407
00:26:35,137 --> 00:26:37,000
I'll go to Kinghorn.

408
00:26:40,586 --> 00:26:43,482
[DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

409
00:26:52,448 --> 00:26:53,827
[BARKING]

410
00:26:59,137 --> 00:27:01,655
I'm home, Ma.

411
00:27:01,793 --> 00:27:04,620
[CHILDREN CHEERING]

412
00:27:13,206 --> 00:27:15,000
GIRLS [IN UNISON]:
Birthday girl first.

413
00:27:15,137 --> 00:27:16,413
You first, Amanda.

414
00:27:25,793 --> 00:27:27,103
I'll get it.

415
00:27:30,103 --> 00:27:33,000
[♪♪♪]

416
00:27:37,862 --> 00:27:41,137
There's someone in there.
There's someone watching me.

417
00:27:41,275 --> 00:27:43,413
You're just saying that
because you missed it,

418
00:27:43,551 --> 00:27:46,275
but since it's your birthday,
you can have another chance.

419
00:27:46,413 --> 00:27:48,137
No, there really was
someone in there.

420
00:27:48,275 --> 00:27:49,931
Well, then let's go see.

421
00:27:50,068 --> 00:27:51,965
No, I think
we should call my mom.

422
00:27:52,103 --> 00:27:53,241
I'll get it.

423
00:27:59,137 --> 00:28:00,758
[ROARS]
[GIRLS SCREAM]

424
00:28:00,896 --> 00:28:03,241
[GIGGLES]
You're such a dork, Amanda.

425
00:28:03,379 --> 00:28:05,448
Now watch how it's done.

426
00:28:12,724 --> 00:28:14,517
You watching, Amanda?

427
00:28:41,827 --> 00:28:43,620
She's over there.

428
00:28:53,827 --> 00:28:57,379
Amanda? Honey, are you okay?
I was worried.

429
00:28:57,517 --> 00:29:00,275
Libby and Tracy said you thought
someone was in the bushes.

430
00:29:00,413 --> 00:29:02,758
He was there, Mommy.
He gave me these.

431
00:29:02,896 --> 00:29:04,724
Who, Amanda?

432
00:29:04,862 --> 00:29:06,172
Who gave you these?

433
00:29:06,310 --> 00:29:08,034
A man in the bushes?
Who was he?

434
00:29:08,172 --> 00:29:09,551
I don't know.
I didn't see him.

435
00:29:09,689 --> 00:29:13,275
Didn't you say Daddy gave me
white roses on my birthday?

436
00:29:13,413 --> 00:29:17,000
Didn't you say he gave me one
for each year?

437
00:29:17,137 --> 00:29:20,931
Yes. Yes, baby, I did.

438
00:29:21,068 --> 00:29:22,172
Yes.

439
00:29:35,827 --> 00:29:38,620
You ever found out what the hell
happened with Ringerman?

440
00:29:38,758 --> 00:29:40,344
Well, he refuses
to speak to anyone

441
00:29:40,482 --> 00:29:43,068
except his lawyer
and the district attorney.

442
00:29:43,206 --> 00:29:44,103
[CHUCKLES]

443
00:29:44,241 --> 00:29:46,206
He's gonna deal, Pete.

444
00:29:46,344 --> 00:29:47,724
Why?

445
00:29:47,862 --> 00:29:49,793
It makes no sense.

446
00:29:49,931 --> 00:29:51,758
I mean, why the hell
is he gonna do that?

447
00:29:51,896 --> 00:29:53,551
He was off.

448
00:29:53,689 --> 00:29:56,275
Good God in heaven,
he was walking.

449
00:29:56,413 --> 00:29:59,896
We gave him every chance, even
getting him with Judge Reasoner.

450
00:30:00,034 --> 00:30:02,206
Does he know the kind of
maneuvering that took?

451
00:30:02,344 --> 00:30:05,275
Well, he doesn't seem to care.

452
00:30:05,413 --> 00:30:08,137
He just wants to make his deal
and do his time.

453
00:30:10,793 --> 00:30:12,000
Wait, what are you doing?

454
00:30:12,137 --> 00:30:15,275
That's a $10,000 piece
of pre-Columbian pottery.

455
00:30:15,413 --> 00:30:16,655
Well, whoever sold you this

456
00:30:16,793 --> 00:30:19,551
should be on
the 10 most wanted.

457
00:30:19,689 --> 00:30:20,965
What about us?

458
00:30:21,103 --> 00:30:22,275
Hmm?

459
00:30:22,413 --> 00:30:24,275
What has Ringerman
going to say about us?

460
00:30:24,413 --> 00:30:26,068
Nothin'.
He won't say anything.

461
00:30:26,206 --> 00:30:29,689
There's no connection,
and we did the right thing.

462
00:30:29,827 --> 00:30:32,413
He'll remember that.
Now, what happened Friday night,

463
00:30:32,551 --> 00:30:36,034
the confession, I don't know
if we'll ever know.

464
00:30:36,172 --> 00:30:37,689
And I don't care.

465
00:30:38,931 --> 00:30:41,103
I heard talk of Cain.

466
00:30:41,241 --> 00:30:43,206
Cain's dead.
Did his name ever come up

467
00:30:43,344 --> 00:30:45,655
in connection with Ringerman?
Maybe.

468
00:30:45,793 --> 00:30:46,655
Yeah.

469
00:30:46,793 --> 00:30:48,862
Maybe or yes? Which?

470
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:51,482
Yes, I think so.
I-- I don't know.

471
00:30:51,620 --> 00:30:52,862
That's all so vague.

472
00:30:53,000 --> 00:30:54,931
What are you worried
about a dead man?

473
00:30:55,068 --> 00:30:58,103
'Cause this wasn't
the first time his name came up.

474
00:31:00,517 --> 00:31:03,862
What if he left
something behind?

475
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:06,172
What if he wrote
something down?

476
00:31:06,310 --> 00:31:09,862
He didn't
have anything towrite down.

477
00:31:10,000 --> 00:31:13,310
Cain was the damn toughest judge
walkin' the earth.

478
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:17,655
You think he would've settled
for a couple of threats

479
00:31:17,793 --> 00:31:21,000
when he could've had us standin'
before him in his own court?

480
00:31:22,517 --> 00:31:25,379
Eventually he would've
turned up somethin',

481
00:31:25,517 --> 00:31:27,000
but he never had anything,

482
00:31:27,137 --> 00:31:29,000
anything concrete,
while he was alive.

483
00:31:29,137 --> 00:31:31,241
There'll never be anything
now that he's dead.

484
00:31:31,379 --> 00:31:32,275
He is dead?

485
00:31:32,413 --> 00:31:34,344
He is dead.

486
00:31:34,482 --> 00:31:36,965
And no matter
what anybody dreams up

487
00:31:37,103 --> 00:31:40,827
or whispers in the streets,
he's staying dead.

488
00:31:43,517 --> 00:31:46,758
All this talk, though,
it's just so crazy,

489
00:31:46,896 --> 00:31:50,137
about the phantom judge
with the face from hell.

490
00:31:51,379 --> 00:31:53,000
Yeah.

491
00:31:54,620 --> 00:31:56,068
What?

492
00:31:56,206 --> 00:31:58,862
The guy I had with me
that night, he must've talked.

493
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:00,689
You never told me
you were there.

494
00:32:00,827 --> 00:32:03,482
I never told you anything.
You never wanted to know.

495
00:32:03,620 --> 00:32:05,275
Like how we used acid...

496
00:32:06,758 --> 00:32:09,379
so everyone would think
that it was a vendetta

497
00:32:09,517 --> 00:32:11,000
and not just
a random homicide.

498
00:32:11,137 --> 00:32:12,137
[SIGHS]

499
00:32:12,275 --> 00:32:13,931
Oh, my God.

500
00:32:16,724 --> 00:32:18,965
You don't have
the stomach for it, huh?

501
00:32:19,103 --> 00:32:22,413
Well, I don't have the stomach
to send a man to his death,

502
