[♪♪♪]

1255
01:15:04,793 --> 01:15:05,724
[GRUNTS]

1256
01:15:06,965 --> 01:15:08,206
Hey, where are you going?

1257
01:15:08,344 --> 01:15:11,241
Oh, uh, did Captain Strauss
come this way?

1258
01:15:11,379 --> 01:15:14,724
Yeah, he said you'd be along.
Oh, he did?

1259
01:15:14,862 --> 01:15:17,655
He told me to send you on down.
Up the corridor to the left.

1260
01:15:17,793 --> 01:15:19,379
Operating Room One.

1261
01:15:19,517 --> 01:15:22,068
Nothin' like a little
police cooperation, right?

1262
01:15:23,413 --> 01:15:24,862
[GROANS]

1263
01:15:25,000 --> 01:15:28,241
[YELLING]

1264
01:15:31,793 --> 01:15:33,931
Look, I wanna
see Tremayne now, okay?

1265
01:15:34,068 --> 01:15:36,482
He'll be right with us.
He said to meet him in OR 1.

1266
01:15:36,620 --> 01:15:37,551
Is that where Cain is?

1267
01:15:37,689 --> 01:15:39,000
[YELLING]

1268
01:15:42,206 --> 01:15:44,000
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

1269
01:15:45,586 --> 01:15:47,000
[GROANING]

1270
01:15:59,517 --> 01:16:01,000
Tremayne?

1271
01:16:02,310 --> 01:16:03,655
Dr. Tremayne?

1272
01:16:08,068 --> 01:16:09,379
Colin?

1273
01:16:11,482 --> 01:16:13,620
Cain?
[GASPS]

1274
01:16:17,586 --> 01:16:19,000
It's me, Cain.

1275
01:16:22,000 --> 01:16:23,896
The one you want, isn't it?

1276
01:16:26,068 --> 01:16:29,172
Come on, let's end
this nightmare, Cain.

1277
01:16:29,310 --> 01:16:33,034
You've been haunting me
for almost a year now. Come on.

1278
01:16:37,758 --> 01:16:38,655
[SOBBING]

1279
01:16:38,793 --> 01:16:41,379
I tried for you, Colin.

1280
01:16:41,517 --> 01:16:43,275
I tried.

1281
01:17:00,620 --> 01:17:03,344
I'm tired
of ghosts and goblins, Cain.

1282
01:17:04,793 --> 01:17:07,034
I'm tired of dead men, Cain.

1283
01:17:09,896 --> 01:17:12,000
Aren't you tired of being one?

1284
01:17:20,413 --> 01:17:22,068
[MUFFLED SCREAMING]

1285
01:17:27,620 --> 01:17:31,103
Remember that family reunion
I promised you?

1286
01:17:31,241 --> 01:17:32,793
[AMANDA WHIMPERING]

1287
01:17:32,931 --> 01:17:34,862
Well, today's the day.

1288
01:17:35,000 --> 01:17:36,793
Don't you wanna say hi
to your daughter

1289
01:17:36,931 --> 01:17:39,689
and goodbye once more, huh?

1290
01:17:39,827 --> 01:17:42,034
Talk to your daddy.
Tell your daddy to come out.

1291
01:17:42,172 --> 01:17:44,206
Come on. Come on.

1292
01:17:45,896 --> 01:17:48,793
Go on. He told you
to call your dad.

1293
01:17:48,931 --> 01:17:50,724
My-- My daddy's dead.

1294
01:17:52,206 --> 01:17:53,620
Well, how right you are.

1295
01:17:53,758 --> 01:17:56,517
Your last chance to look, Cain!
[AMANDA WHIMPERING]

1296
01:17:56,655 --> 01:17:59,586
[♪♪♪]

1297
01:18:06,862 --> 01:18:08,103
Stop fighting, you little--

1298
01:18:08,241 --> 01:18:09,413
All right, take it easy.

1299
01:18:09,551 --> 01:18:10,827
Now you just watch the door.

1300
01:18:10,965 --> 01:18:12,448
This is an operating room.

1301
01:18:12,586 --> 01:18:15,206
An emergency generator
should kick on.

1302
01:18:18,655 --> 01:18:20,655
[WHIRRING]

1303
01:18:28,310 --> 01:18:29,724
[WHIMPERING]

1304
01:18:44,241 --> 01:18:46,068
Now, keep that kid still.

1305
01:18:47,689 --> 01:18:48,689
[♪♪♪]

1306
01:18:48,827 --> 01:18:51,034
[MUFFLED GROANING]

1307
01:18:57,275 --> 01:18:58,689
Wes?

1308
01:18:58,827 --> 01:19:02,482
CAIN:
I told you
I'd come back for you, Strauss,

1309
01:19:02,620 --> 01:19:05,482
from the grave, if necessary.

1310
01:19:05,620 --> 01:19:07,103
[GUNSHOT]

1311
01:19:07,241 --> 01:19:09,586
Face me. Face me, damn you!

1312
01:19:09,724 --> 01:19:12,551
You want me, you got me. Why
don't you stand up and face me?

1313
01:19:12,689 --> 01:19:14,206
You wanted me?[GASPS]

1314
01:19:14,344 --> 01:19:15,724
You've got me.

1315
01:19:17,482 --> 01:19:18,724
[GASPS]

1316
01:19:20,551 --> 01:19:23,172
[♪♪♪]

1317
01:19:24,793 --> 01:19:26,241
[HISSING]

1318
01:19:28,448 --> 01:19:30,137
Watch her die, Cain!

1319
01:19:33,482 --> 01:19:36,517
Cain!

1320
01:19:48,275 --> 01:19:50,758
[SCREAMING]

1321
01:20:08,896 --> 01:20:11,310
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

1322
01:20:11,448 --> 01:20:12,965
Oh!
AMANDA: No, no.

1323
01:20:13,103 --> 01:20:14,689
Are you okay? You okay?
No, no, no.

1324
01:20:14,827 --> 01:20:16,620
Oh, no, I'm a friend.
[SOBBING]

1325
01:20:16,758 --> 01:20:18,689
Oh, I knew your father.

1326
01:20:18,827 --> 01:20:20,758
Oh! Oh...

1327
01:20:22,724 --> 01:20:23,655
Are you okay?

1328
01:20:23,793 --> 01:20:26,000
Now that that monster's
gone away.

1329
01:20:26,137 --> 01:20:27,965
Let's go home.

1330
01:20:28,103 --> 01:20:31,000
[♪♪♪]

1331
01:20:59,896 --> 01:21:01,896
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

1332
01:21:24,241 --> 01:21:25,758
Anything I say...

1333
01:21:25,896 --> 01:21:28,586
Anything I try
to say will sound inane.

1334
01:21:28,724 --> 01:21:30,517
I know that you can
never understand

1335
01:21:30,655 --> 01:21:32,275
what you've done for me.

1336
01:21:32,413 --> 01:21:33,896
Just this morning...

1337
01:21:34,034 --> 01:21:35,275
I mean, just this morning

1338
01:21:35,413 --> 01:21:39,000
I thought my life
as I knew it was over.

1339
01:21:39,137 --> 01:21:40,931
Looking across at my home,

1340
01:21:41,068 --> 01:21:43,000
knowing Susie and Lisa
are waiting for me,

1341
01:21:43,137 --> 01:21:44,862
that I'm gonna
walk through that door

1342
01:21:45,000 --> 01:21:47,620
like I have
so many other times...

1343
01:21:47,758 --> 01:21:49,000
I feel reborn.

1344
01:21:51,517 --> 01:21:54,344
When I truly lost all hope,

1345
01:21:54,482 --> 01:21:56,655
you've given me
a second chance at life.

1346
01:21:56,793 --> 01:21:59,172
What can I do
to thank you for that?

1347
01:21:59,310 --> 01:22:00,827
Use it.

1348
01:22:00,965 --> 01:22:03,241
How will I find you again?

1349
01:22:03,379 --> 01:22:06,034
How do I contact you?
What if I need you?

1350
01:22:06,172 --> 01:22:08,103
You won't need me, Walter.

1351
01:22:08,241 --> 01:22:10,241
You won't need me.

1352
01:22:10,379 --> 01:22:13,620
And if you do,
I'll be listening.

1353
01:22:13,758 --> 01:22:15,034
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

1354
01:22:23,172 --> 01:22:24,413
Thanks.

1355
01:22:26,103 --> 01:22:27,655
Someone's waiting for you.

1356
01:22:36,689 --> 01:22:38,448
Daddy! Daddy's home!

1357
01:22:41,862 --> 01:22:44,172
[♪♪♪]

1358
01:22:58,000 --> 01:22:59,551
There is still 
much to be unraveled

1359
01:22:59,689 --> 01:23:01,482
in this truly bizarre 
turn of events

1360
01:23:01,620 --> 01:23:03,586
connected with 
the Grim Reaper murders,

1361
01:23:03,724 --> 01:23:06,551
but it is suspected that the 
man who kidnapped Amanda Cain,

1362
01:23:06,689 --> 01:23:08,724
daughter of 
the late Judge Paul Cain,

1363
01:23:08,862 --> 01:23:12,206
was indeed a city police 
officer named Kevin Wesley.

1364
01:23:12,344 --> 01:23:13,931
Wesley died tonight 
in the fire

1365
01:23:14,068 --> 01:23:16,724
at the Broadmoor Institute, 
along with Captain Strauss,

1366
01:23:16,862 --> 01:23:19,758
Dr. Colin Tremayne 
and Dr. Tanya Russell.

1367
01:23:19,896 --> 01:23:21,758
There are 
unsubstantiated rumors

1368
01:23:21,896 --> 01:23:23,689
that Dr. Tremayne 
is going to be named

1369
01:23:23,827 --> 01:23:25,413
in connection 
with the Reaper murders

1370
01:23:25,551 --> 01:23:27,862
along with his sister, 
Dr. Tanya Russell,

1371
01:23:28,000 --> 01:23:30,000
who also worked 
at the institute.

1372
01:23:30,137 --> 01:23:32,068
It is believed 
they conspired together

1373
01:23:32,206 --> 01:23:34,310
to have one of their patients, 
Walter Donovan,

1374
01:23:34,448 --> 01:23:36,827
convicted of the heinous 
Reaper crime.

1375
01:23:36,965 --> 01:23:39,000
I-- I have no idea 
what happened or why.

1376
01:23:39,137 --> 01:23:40,517
I-- I was out for the evening

1377
01:23:40,655 --> 01:23:42,206
and someone came 
to the babysitter

1378
01:23:42,344 --> 01:23:44,586
and identified themselves 
as a police officer

1379
01:23:44,724 --> 01:23:50,206
and took my daughter, and... 
Oh!

1380
01:23:50,344 --> 01:23:52,551
Why Amanda Cain was taken 
from her home tonight

1381
01:23:52,689 --> 01:23:54,448
is a complete mystery.

1382
01:23:54,586 --> 01:23:57,517
Why did that man say
I was gonna meet Daddy?

1383
01:23:57,655 --> 01:24:01,586
For a minute he made me think
Daddy wasalive.

1384
01:24:01,724 --> 01:24:05,620
I can't explain why people do
such cruel things, honey.

1385
01:24:05,758 --> 01:24:07,379
They're sick people.
They need help.

1386
01:24:07,517 --> 01:24:11,275
And sometimes innocent people
get hurt by their illness.

1387
01:24:11,413 --> 01:24:14,586
But you don't
have anything to worry about.

1388
01:24:14,724 --> 01:24:18,137
I'm here, and I love you.

1389
01:24:18,275 --> 01:24:21,310
Will you stay with me
for a while? I'm afraid.

1390
01:24:21,448 --> 01:24:24,241
Afraid of the monster.
Oh, sure, baby.

1391
01:24:24,379 --> 01:24:26,620
I'm just gonna make sure
the door's locked, okay?

1392
01:24:26,758 --> 01:24:27,724
I'll be right back.

1393
01:24:27,862 --> 01:24:29,344
But what if
the monster comes back?

1394
01:24:29,482 --> 01:24:32,793
Oh, honey, mmm! He won't.

1395
01:24:35,275 --> 01:24:37,068
I'll be one minute.

1396
01:24:41,241 --> 01:24:45,965
Here, while I'm gone,
you hold this.

1397
01:24:46,103 --> 01:24:48,586
You don't have
anything to worry about.

1398
01:24:48,724 --> 01:24:51,000
What do I always tell you?

1399
01:24:51,137 --> 01:24:52,758
Daddy watches over us.

1400
01:24:54,241 --> 01:24:58,172
And Daddy will protect you
from the monster, okay?

1401
01:24:58,310 --> 01:24:59,655
Mmm.

1402
01:25:05,482 --> 01:25:08,482
You'll protect me
from the monster, Daddy.

1403
01:25:08,620 --> 01:25:10,517
You'll protect me.

1404
01:25:10,655 --> 01:25:13,586
[♪♪♪]

1405
01:25:23,689 --> 01:25:26,620
[♪♪♪]

